HEADWORD: Gynocracy
<hw>Gy*noc"ra*cy</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧*n⟦ocr⟧k"r⟦adot⟧*s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Gynecocracy</er>.]</ety> <def>Female
government; gynecocracy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The aforesaid state has repeatedly changed from absolute despotism
to republicanism, not forgetting the intermediate stages of oligarchy,
limited monarchy, and even <qex>gynocracy</qex>; for I myself remember
Alsatia governed for nearly nine months by an old fishwoman.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gynodioecious</ent>⟦br⟧
